               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370703-name-612" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370703-name-612" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370703-name-612" type="surname" value="COLSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370703-name-612" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>SARAH COLSON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a widow, and live at No. 4, Trafalgar-row, Wal<lb></lb>worth, in the parish of St. Mary, Newington. I keep a coal-shed, and the prisoner was my errand-by for two years and a half—I gave him 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. a week, and his ten and supper—on the 14th of June I went out in the morning for about twenty minutes—when I returned the prisoner was standing at the door-post—he went out the back way and absconded—I went up stairs in less than a quarter of an hour, and missed the money stated in the indictment from a drawer in my back room, and six spoons—I received information, and went to No. 4, George-street, with a policeman, and took the prisoner—I had left no one at home but him and a little infant, who was asleep—he had opened the drawer with a knife.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370703-name-613" type="witnessName">
